reach the tops to view nothing but more hills.  Far to the north, a freezing
fog obscurs your view of the mountains.
  }
  sector { arctic }
  exits {
	to { n, 9 }
	to { e, 10 }
	to { w, 3 }
  }
}

7
{
  name { The Tundra  }
  desc {
You climb yet another hill and look out to the west to see the tundra spreads
on endlessly to the horizon.  You feel no need to test it's mighty length. 
To the north a dense, cold fog obscurs your view of the mountain range.
  }
  sector { arctic }
  exits {
	to { n, 11 }
	to { e, 5 }
  }
}

8
{
  name { The Tundra  }
  desc {
"   The tundra spreads out around in all directions giving you nothing but an
endless view of hills and gullies. The wind sweeps these lands biting deep to
bone. You feel that should anything live here it must lead a lonely life.
Just to the north, a thick icy fog obscurs your view of the mountain range.
  }
  sector { arctic }
  exits {
	to { n, 16 }
	to { e, 4 }
	to { s, 5 }
	to { w, 11 }
  }
}

9
{
  name { The Tundra  }
  desc {
"  The vast wastes of the tundra send your mind reeling as you try to take in
their emmense size. All around you they spread giving nothing except the view
on rolling hills covered in long flowing brown grass and dirty ice.  Just to
the north a curtain of icy fog obscurs your view of the mountain range.
  }
  sector { arctic }
  exits {
	to { n, 14 }
	to { e, 12 }
	to { s, 6 }
	to { w, 4 }
  }
}

10
{
  name { The Tundra  }
  desc {
"  You climb yet more hills to witness the tundra running of to the east beyond
imagining. You see no point on continuing in that direction and turn north
deeper into the tundra vast wastes.  Just to the north a vast billowing fog
obscurs your view of the mountain range.
  }
  sector { arctic }
  exits {
	to { n, 12 }
	to { w, 6 }
  }
}

11
{
  name { The Tundra  }
  desc {
"   The tundra sprawls out around as far as the eye can see leaving you dwarfed
by it's vast and times body. All around the hills role on giving no sign of
life.  Just to the north a vast wall of icy fog obscurs your view of the range
of mountains.
  }
  sector { arctic }
  exits {
	to { n, 17 }
	to { e, 8 }
	to { s, 7 }
  }
}

12
{
  name { The Tundra  }
  desc {
"   You begin to feel lonely upon this vast sweeping grass land as all you see
before is the endless rise and fall of the grassy hill like the one upon
which you now stand.  The wind has picked up it's tempo and you are forced
to pull your cloak tight around to protect from it's icy bite.  Just to the
north a wall of icy fog lies like a soft blanket across the land.
  }
  sector { arctic }
  exits {
	to { n, 13 }
	to { s, 10 }
	to { w, 9 }
  }
}

13
{
  name { Inside the Fog on the Tundra  }
  desc {
"   The fog here obscures everything.  The cold is so bitter that it seeps
between your clothes and chills your bones.  The air is still.  Something
seems out of place.  Perhaps heading south to the Tundra would be a good
idea.
  }
  sector { cold }
  exits {
	to { n, 22 }
	to { s, 12 }
	to { w, 14 }
  }
}

14
{
  name { Inside the Fog on the Tundra  }
  desc {
"   The bleak wall of white, freezing fog prevents you seeing far in any
direction.  The air is so bitterly cold that it seems to bite you.  You
are sure that this would be a truly lonely place to die.
  }
  sector { cold }
  exits {
	to { n, 21 }
	to { e, 13 }
	to { s, 9 }
	to { w, 15 }
  }
}

15
{
  name { Inside the Fog on the Tundra  }
  desc {
"   Cold seeps endlessly in to your bones, freezing you where you stand.
Finding a way out of this forsaken Tundra would be a good idea.
  }
  sector { cold }
  exits {
	to { n, 20 }
	to { e, 14 }
	to { s, 4 }
	to { w, 16 }
  }
}

16
{
  name { Inside the Fog on the Tundra  }
  desc {
"  You begin to wonder if this vast fog will ever thin.  It almost
seems to stick to you like a misty blanket, dampening your vision.
  }
  sector { cold }
  exits {
	to { n, 19 }
	to { e, 15 }
	to { s, 8 }
	to { w, 17 }
  }
}

17
{
  name { Inside the Fog on the Tundra  }
  desc {
"   You begin to feel fatigued at the sheer task of traversing this unforgiving
and desolate land.  Freezing fog chills you to the very bone.
  }
  sector { cold }
  exits {
	to { n, 18 }
	to { e, 16 }
	to { s, 11 }
  }
}

18
{
  name { Before a glacial wall  }
  desc {
"  Finally you find something to break the weary monotony of this vast tundra
and thick, murky fog.  Rising out of the gloom to the north you see a large
glacier that has eaten it's way down a valley channel.  The front of this
glacier is potted with fissures and a single, large, looming cavern entrance.
  }
  sector { cold }
  exits {
	to { e, 19 }
	to { s, 17 }
	to { 10, 63 }
      info { secret, hidden }
      keywords { cavern }
  }
  extra {
	keywords { cavern glacier fissures entrance }
	desc { 
"
There is a large, looming cavern entrance in the face of the glacier wall.
You could probably 'go cavern' and enter it.  There might be some nice
treasure inside for you to steal.  Yes, steal.  There, I said it.  You call
yourself an adventurer but really you're just a high-class thief taking
other peoples stuff and then passing it off as your own.

"	}
  }
}

19
{
  name { Inside the Fog on the Tundra  }
  desc {
"  The vast expanse of fog you have become so accustomed too seems to have
no end in sight.  It hides deep crevasses and other perilous things that you
can't see until you are right on top of them.  Is there a way out?
  }
  sector { cold }
  exits {
	to { e, 20 }
	to { s, 16 }
	to { w, 18 }
  }
}

20
{
  name { Inside the Fog on the Tundra  }
  desc {
"   Have you been here before?  It is impossible to tell with the fog
obscuring everything in every direction.
  }
  sector { cold }
  exits {
	to { e, 21 }
	to { s, 15 }
	to { w, 19 }
  }
}

21
{
  name { A trail to the north.  }
  desc {
"  The fog finally thins, allowing you to view a trial leading upwards in to
a mountainous pass.  The air looks crisp and sharp to the north, and maybe it
might even be warmer.  
  }
  sector { cold }
  exits {
	to { n, 23 }
	to { e, 22 }
	to { s, 14 }
	to { w, 20 }
  }
}

22
{
  name { The Tundra  }
  desc {
"   The vast tundra gives way to the rockier ground as you begin to rise into
the foothills of the mountains to the north. You are forced to turn west when
you find no trails to lead you into the mountains.  Still the bank of fog
offers no respite to your tired eyes.
  }
  sector { cold }
  exits {
	to { s, 13 }
	to { w, 21 }
  }
}

23
{
  name { A Mountain Pass  }
  desc {
"   You have entered a large mountain pass that is flanked on both sides by
huge cliff faces that tower above you.  To the north you can see what appears
to be a huge stone structure that blocks off the entire northern end of the
pass.  To the south is a rocky mountain trail that leads down to the tundra
and back in to the freezing, murky fog.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  extra {
  	keywords { door doors structure stone }
  	desc { 
"   This giant stone structure is actually a set of gates that have closed to
block off the pass from invaders.  They are mighty affairs, with stones and
iron bindings.  But a simple, un-pickable lock keeps the riff-raff out (or 
in).
  	}
  }
  exits {
	to { n, 24 }
	  key { 16202 }
	  info { door, closed, locked, autolock, autoclose, pickproof }
	  keywords { doors }
	to { s, 21 }
  }
}

24
{
  name { A Guard Post  }
  desc {
"  You are standing in what appears to be some sort of guard post. On both
sides are small (for a giant) alcoves that have been hollowed out in a such
a way as to provide a place to stand, sit or sleep for any oversize guards
that are on duty.  To the south are a set of mighty stone doors that block
off access to the Tundra beyond.  To the north the trail, now quite well
and well maintained, leads in to a mountain valley.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  extra {
  	keywords { door doors structure stone }
  	desc { 
"   This giant stone structure is actually a set of gates that have closed to
block off the gorge from invaders.  They are mighty affairs, with stones and
iron bindings.  But a simple, un-pickable lock keeps the riff-raff out (or 
in).
  	}
  }
  exits {
	to { n, 25 }
	to { s, 23 }
	  key { 16202 }
	  info { door, closed, locked, autolock, autoclose, pickproof }
	  keywords { doors }
  }
}

25
{
  name { The Valley Crossroads  }
  desc {
"   You stand at a crossroads at the bottom of a deep mountain valley.  Far To
the north you can see a well-maintained causeway leading up to a large long-
house set in to the mountains' face.  To the east the trail heads off in a
downwards slope towards the base of the mountain, whilst to the west the trail
rises up towards the valley tops where low hanging, thick storm clouds hover
ominously.  And to the south stand a massive set of gates that protect this
picturesque valley from the likes of you.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  exits {
	to { n, 26 }
	to { e, 28 }
	to { s, 24 }
	to { w, 27 }
  }
}

26
{
  name { The giant Causeway  }
  desc {
"   You are standing on a wide, giant causeway that is flanked on each side by
large round houses with timber walls and thick, warm thatch roofs.  Judging by
sheer size of the abodes, the dwellers must stand at least twice as tall as you
easily.  To the north the causeway leads to a huge set of doors that mark the
entrance to an over-sized long-house that has been built in to the very side of
the mountain itself.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  exits {
	to { n, 29 }
	to { s, 25 }
  }
}

27
{
  name { Higher up the valley side }
  desc {
"   You are standing on an ill-maintained path roughly half-way up the side
of the steep mountain valley.  Below you can see the crossroads to the east
and the long-house further to the north, it's gigantic structure built into
the very sides of the mountain.  The path veers off northwards and up here,
towards the gusty valley top where ominous-looking storm clouds gather and
blow at mountains as if to topple them. To the southwest is a low, conical
cave that reeks of sulphur and burning pitch.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  exits {
	to { n, 33 }
	to { e, 25 }
	to { southwest, 34 }
  }
}

28
{
  name { The Valley Road  }
  desc {
"   You are standing on the road at the very base of the valley.  Large round
houses made of stone with thatch roofs dot the sides of the track here and
there, but none of them looking interesting enough to enter.  Here the road
heads west to the valley crossroads or east towards the mountain road where,
to the east and south, a mighty forge has been constructed that belches out
thick black clouds of soot and smoke.  You can hear the ringing of hammers
even from here.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  exits {
	to { e, 36 }
	to { w, 25 }
	to { 10, 77 }
	  info { hidden, secret }
	  keywords { opening }
  }
  extra {
    keywords { roundhouse house }
	desc {
"
The Roundhouses are all made of stone with mouldy old straw roofs.  Fires
lit on the inside cause the straw and thatch to steam and smoke as the fumes
escape in to the air.  There is a small #{bold}opening#{o} that could be entered if an
adventurer like you so wanted. 
"
	}
  }
}

29
{
  name { Before the doors of Helsengard  }
  desc {
"   To the north of you stand the doors of Helsengard, the long-house home and
the council centre for the dwellers of this place.  It's walls are rock-hard
mottle and daub, oak timbers and shale, all carved with the likenesses of
fierce angular dragons.  It is an imposing obstacle to pass.  The doors seem
to be locked... But who would want a burgle such a place?
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  extra {
  	keywords { door doors long house longhouse }
  	desc { 
"   The doors to the long house are huge, towering up at least twenty feet,
and are barred with iron.  A gigantic, stylised dragon with five heads has
been carved in to the wood in a Game of Thrones knock-off style that makes
you think of strange lands, scantily clad ladies and blue-eyed zombies.  The
doors are locked.  You'll need a key to get in there.
  	}
  }  
  exits {
	to { n, 30 }
	  key { 16203 }
	  info { door, closed, autoclose, locked, autolock, pickproof }
	  keywords { door }
	to { s, 26 }
  }
}

30
{
  name { The Great Hall  }
  desc {
"   This is the Great Hall of Helsengard.  A fire pit, surrounded by benches
and tables that dwarf you, throws off enough to singe away your eyebrows.
The great room stretches off to the west and east, the flames from the
fire put acting like a runway that casts a ruddy glow off to in to the
alternate directions.  You can leave east.  Or west.  It's a hard life
having to make all these decisions, isn't it?
  }
  sector { ship_deck }
  extra {
  	keywords { door doors }
  	desc { 
"   This giant doors have been made... Well... For a giant.  They tower up
in to the smokey, murky, depths of the ceiling, at least twenty feet high
and are barred with iron.  The wood is plain on this side, but clearly very
thick and hard.  An effective lock acts as a simple means to keep burglars
out.  After all, one never knows what the kids around here will nick these
days.
  	}
  }  
  flags { indoors }
  exits {
	to { e, 32 }
	to { s, 29 }
	  key { 16203 }
	  info { door, closed, autoclose, locked, autolock, pickproof }
	  keywords { door }
	to { w, 31 }
  }
}

31
{
  name { The West End of the Great Hall  }
  desc {
"   This is the west end of the great hall.  Chairs, benches, tables and
sorts line the fire pit.  The atmosphere is warm, cosy and if you were
to stay too long, would likely be sleepy too.  This place is perfect
for those long drawn out conversations and arguments about the price
of wheat, who stole whose goat and how to invade Midgard with a bunch
of evil black skinned Drow.
  }
  sector { ship_deck }
  flags { indoors }
  exits {
	to { e, 30 }
  }
}

32
{
  name { The East End of the Great Hall  }
  desc {
"   The east end of the great hall is where the women and children can be
found, feasting, fighting and quaffing ale with the same enthusiasm as
the males.  Not that it makes much difference for the giants what your
gender is, that seems to be a human problem.  The fire pit casts it's
bright, hot glow over everything, making the whole hall an inviting and
cheerful place.  At least, inviting for anyone over ten-feet in height.
  }
  sector { ship_deck }
  flags { indoors }
  exits {
	to { w, 30 }
  }
}

33
{
  name { A Windy Valley Path  }
  desc {
"   You are standing on a windy, gusty, valley path that leads up to the
summit of the valley tops where dark grey storm clouds scud across the
rocky hills in a never-ending battle for supremacy.  The ground is made
up of loose shale and pebbles, perfect for slipping on and breaking a
leg, an arm, or even your neck.  You can head up to the valley top, or
down to the valley sides and the eventual evenness of the valley floor.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  exits {
	to { s, 27 }
	to { w, 35 }
  }
}

34
{
  name { The Nest of Gnatt  }
  desc {
"   You are standing in a giant, disgusting nest.  There is no other means
to describe it.  The floor is littered with bones of all sizes, showing that
whatever calls this place home is probably capable of taking care of itself.
A crack in the south wall of the nest, that might be big enough for you to 
squeeze through, belches out hot, noxious fumes that makes the nest smell
like Bunta's toilet.  The rest of the detritus that litters here is made up
of mildewed straw and other rotting plant-life that seems to form a soft,
damp and smelly bed.
  }
  sector { Cavern }
  exits {
    to { northeast, 27 }
	to { 10, 64 }
      info { secret, hidden, message }
      keywords { shimmy }
  }
  extra {
	keywords { crack wall }
	desc { 
"
There is a crack running the entire length of the south wall of this nest.
Yes, that's right, length.  Meaning you're not sidling in like a burglar in
the night, you're going to have to #{bold}shimmy#{o} in on your belly and hope you're
not caught prone if there is anything beyond.  Thick, hot clouds of sulphur
billow out from it.  Will the air be safe to breathe in there?

"	}
  	keywords { _ex10 }
  	desc {  "
	
#{yellow}You shimmy in to the crack... 

For a moment you wish you followed that New Years diet plan...

It's a tight squeeze but... POP!#{o}

"   }
  }
}

35
{
  name { The Valley Top  }
  desc {
"   This is the top of the valley.  The storm clouds are so close here you
could almost step on to them as they whistle, hiss and scud against the
rocks at the top here.  It is cold and blowy, but the air is crisp and
clean and gives you a wonderful view of the valley below.  You can exit
down the path here towards the valley floor.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  exits {
	to { e, 33 }
	to { 10, 65 }
	  info { hidden, secret, message }
	  keywords { float }
  }
  extra { 
	keywords { clouds storm }
	desc { 
"
The clouds here never seem to lose their grip on the valley top.  In
fact, they appear to be attached to it.  Magic perhaps?  Who knows.
But you it is possible you could #{bold}float#{o} your way over to them if you
had the ability to fly...

"
	}
	keywords { _ex10 }
	desc {  "
	  
#{cyan}Laughing like a child you deftly float from the ground to the cloud.

How cool is that??#{o}	  
	  
"   }
    keywords { valley floor mountain }
	desc {  
"
The valley is perfectly visible from here.  You can see the trail down from
your vantage point and follow as it worms it's way north to the long house
built in to the mountain wall itself.  You can see the billow of translucent
yellowy sulphur and brimstone from the conical cave of the valley side.  The
dark black smoke from the forge (although you are too far away for the sound
to reach here) that resides like a cancerous smudge to the south-east of the
valley.  And you can even see the looming gates that lead in to the mountain
of Pyragard itself, standing out in reds and golds that gleam and sparkle in
the distance.  If you had a way to record this view, you surely would.

" 
	}
  }
}

36
{
  name { The Mountain Road  }
  desc {
"   The road is intercepted here by a mountain road running from north to south
and heading deep into the mountain range to the north.  To the south you can
see a mighty forge bellowing out thick, dirty black clouds of soot, smoke and
steam.  The ringing of hammers and industriousness fills the air.  Well that
just HAS to be worth a visit!  You can exit south to the forge or head north
and follow the mountain road where it eventually leads into the depths of
Mount Pyragard itself.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  exits {
	to { n, 39 }
	to { s, 37 }
	to { w, 28 }
  }
}

37
{
  name { The Forge  }
  desc {
"   You are standing in what appears to be a giant forge.  Ironic as you
are clearly in giant lands.  All around you is the clash of hammer on steel
as the industry of war churns out it's produce.  But this is no ordinary
forge.  Dark figures, shorter than a human, flitter from machine to anvil,
press to trough, adjusting works, adding things to the mixes of molten metals
that light up the building with an eerie orange glow.
  }
  sector { ship_deck }
  flags { indoors }
  exits {
	to { n, 36 }
	to { s, 38 }
  }
}

38
{
  name { The Foundry  }
  desc {
"   Complimenting the forge to the north is the foundry, where ore dug from
the depths of Mount Pyragard by the fire giants is turned in to the useful
materials needed to make iron and steel.  The materials of war.  The heat in
this place is oppressive.  Ugh.
  }
  sector { ship_deck }
  flags { indoors }
  exits {
	to { n, 37 }
  }
}

39
{
  name { Mountain road  }
  desc {
"   This mountain road winds it way through the mountain passes and gorges
giving you wonderful views of the snow capped mountain peak that towers above
you.  Away to the south, the distant sound of hammering and industry can be
heard.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  exits {
	to { n, 40 }
	to { s, 36 }
  }
}

40
{
  name { Mountain Pass  }
  desc {
"   You stand upon a mountain trail that leads off deep into the heart of the
mountain.  To the northeast you can just about see the trail disappear around
the corner of the mountain face.  To the south you see a well maintained 
mountain road.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  exits {
	to { s, 39 }
	to { northeast, 41 }
  }
}

41
{
  name { A Mountain Ledge  }
  desc {
"   You find yourself at the bottom of a small cliff face.  Above you there is
a small ledge or plateau.  To the southwest a mountain trail leads on into the
mountain valley.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  exits {
	to { u, 42 }
	to { southwest, 40 }
  }
}

42
{
  name { Mountain Entrance  }
  desc {
"   You are standing at the top of a small cliff with an entrance in to the
mountain to the north.  From this entrance issues a warm and scented breeze.
Below you at the base of the cliff you can see a small mountain trail.  The
entrance is sealed by a portcullis.  There seems to be no way around to get
around it without a key.
  }
  sector { Mountains }
  exits {
	to { n, 44 }
	  key { 16204 }
      info { door, closed, autoclose, locked, autolock, pickproof }
      keywords { portcullis }
	to { d, 41 }
  }
}

43
{
  name { A downward shaft  }
  desc {
"   You are standing above a large, circular shaft that has been built in to
floor.  Although you can see nothing in the darkness below you, a fierce heat
blows up from below as if driven on invisible air currents.  A wide, but crude,
stair has been cut in to the side of the shaft, spiralling around and leading
downwards.  To the south the light from the entrance is bright and welcoming.
  }
  flags { dark, indoors }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
	to { s, 44 }
	to { d, 45 }
  }
}

44
{
  name { Inside the Mountain }
  desc {
"   You are standing inside of Mount Pyragard itself.  Impressive enough on
the outside, the inside is just wondrous; filled with rocks, pebbles, the
odd dead insect.  You truly are an explorer like no-one before.  Remarkable
how this hasn't all been named after you.  From the north the air is hot and
dry, whilst to the south it tastes fresh and clean.  A portcullis, embedded
in to the rock, prevents you leaving south.  Unless you have a key that is.
  }
  flags { dark }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
	to { n, 43 }
	to { s, 42 }
	  key { 16204 }
	  info { door, closed, autoclose, locked, autolock, pickproof }
	  keywords { portcullis }
  }
}

45
{
  name { Bottom of the shaft  }
  desc {
"   You are standing at the bottom of a deep and roughly hewn shaft.  The air
is stifling hot and the breeze is the merest hint of movement across your
skin.  Aside from that there isn't much to see.  The walls are rock.  The
ceiling is rock.  The floor is rock.  That might be a pebble over there,
otherwise I think you'll find it's mostly rock.
  }
  flags { dark, indoors, private }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
	to { e, 46 }
	to { u, 43 }
  }
}

46
{
  name { A Hot Tunnel  }
  desc {
"   You are standing at the a turning in a stiflingly hot tunnel.  Away to
the north you can make out the eerie red glow of flames.  The gentle, almost
soothing hiss of flames can be heard.  But not much else.  There's a lot of
rock around you, which is unsurprising as you are deep within the mountain
known as Pyragard.
  }
  flags { dark, indoors, private }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
	to { n, 47 }
	to { w, 45 }
  }
}

47
{
  name { The Bridge of Flames  }
  desc {
"   A thin span of rock, no more than the width of an elven foot, bridges
the gap here between the tunnel to the south and the complex of caves to
the north.  Below, at least one hundred feet away, a river of lava flows,
slow and thick like custard poured over a cake.  It wouldn't be a great
idea to fall off here.
  }
  sector { Fire }
  flags { private, indoors }
  exits {
	to { n, 48 }
	to { s, 46 }
  }
}

48
{
  name { The Fire Caves  }
  desc {
"   The fire caves, the home of the Fire Giants, the most terrible of all
the giantkin that roam Mount Pyragard, the rocky valley, the thunderous
cloudscape and the icy tundra waste.  The caves are man (or giant) made,
hewn from the rock and smoothed over centuries of use.  You're sure to
find something to endanger down here.
  }
  sector { cavern }
  flags { indoors }
  exits {
	to { n, 49 }
	to { s, 47 }
  }
}

49
{
  name { Inside the Fire Caves  }
  desc {
"   You are standing at a junction inside the fire caves of the fire
giants--as unimaginative as that sounds.  There are amazingly no sign
posts to help guide your way.  You can exit west, where a fiery glow
warms the way, or east, where a fiery glow doesn't warm the way, or
south, where yes, another fiery glow warms the way.  These options will
of course help to narrow down your choices.  }
  flags { private, indoors }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
	to { e, 51 }
	to { s, 48 }
	to { w, 60 }
  }
}

50
{
  name { Sanctuary  }
  desc {
"   You are standing in a small but cool chamber that is too big to allow
Tiamat to enter.  This is lucky for you.  Perhaps you can rest here and
consider a way to get out without being eaten.
  }
  flags { indoors, tunnel, private, fast_mana, fast_hit_points, fast_moves, blue_glow, evil_altar, good_altar, neutral_altar, no_mob }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
    to { southeast, 59 }
  }
}

51
{
  name { Inside the Fire Caves  }
  desc {
"   You head east along the causeway being dazzled by the display of fire that
erupts from the blow holes along the roadside, to light your way. Leaving
you with brilliant after images as they subside. The road here continues to
the east and also turns north. It is from the east that the sounds of anguish
and torment you have heard since entering Pyragard seem to be emanating.
  }
  flags { private, indoors }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
	to { n, 52 }
	to { e, 53 }
	to { w, 49 }
  }
}

52
{
  name { Inside the Fire Caves }
  desc {
"   You are standing in a tunnel inside the fire caves.  It is not exciting.
To the south you can see that the tunnel branches off at a junction point and
away to the north it turns east.  Oooh whatever will you decide to do.
  }
  flags { private, indoors }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
	to { n, 56 }
	to { s, 51 }
  }
}

53
{
  name { Inside the Fire Caves  }
  desc {
"   The eastern end of the fire caves end here with a door leading south.
However, the door is locked, barred and heavily fortified, no doubt forcing
you to go and find a key from some obscure monster to open it with.  You can
exit west.
  }
  flags { private, indoors }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
	to { s, 54 }
	  key { 16205 }
      info { door, closed, autoclose, locked, autolock, pickproof }
      keywords { prison }
	to { w, 51 }
  }
}

54
{
  name { Inside this Prison  }
  desc {
"   This room is hot beyond belief.  The walls shimmer and waver with steam
that rises from the floor.  Everything is burning.  Only a crude cut bench
offers any prisoner in this place any kind of opportunity to sit and rest.
You certainly wouldn't want to face a life-time in here, you'd be hard-
boiled in a week.
  }
  sector { Fire }
  flags { private, indoors }
  exits {
	to { n, 53 }
	  key { 16205 }
      info { door, closed, autoclose, locked, autolock, pickproof }
      keywords { prison }
  }
}

55
{
  name { Sanctuary  }
  desc {
"   You are standing in a small but cool chamber that is too big to allow
Tiamat to enter.  This is lucky for you.  Perhaps you can rest here and
consider a way to get out without being eaten.
  }
  flags { indoors, tunnel, private, fast_mana, fast_hit_points, fast_moves, blue_glow, evil_altar, good_altar, neutral_altar, no_mob }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
    to { southwest, 59 }
  }
}

56
{
  name { Inside the Fire Caves  }
  desc {
"   You are standing in a tunnel system inside the fire caves.  There's not
much to see.  The tunnel heads off east and south.  Choices choices.
  }
  flags { private, indoors }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
	to { e, 57 }
	to { s, 52 }
  }
}

57
{
  name { Inside the Fire Caves  }
  desc {
"   Interestingly enough you are in a tunnel.  Inside the fire caves.  What
makes this any different to the myriad of other tunnels in the fire caves?
Well now, I am glad you asked.  Away to the north you can make out a door.
Or a dam.  It is huge, towering, beyond words to describe.  The tunnel widens
like the top of a funnel, spreading outwards in a conical fashion.  That has
to be a worth a look?
  }
  flags { private, indoors }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
	to { n, 58 }
	to { w, 56 }
  }
}

58
{
  name { Gates of Pyrax  }
  desc {
"   Legend tells that the Gates of Pyrax are the mythical boundary between
this realm and the realms of the Gods.  If that is true, then you have stepped
in to myth right here.  Before you a giant dam-like gate rises up over one
hundred feet in to the air.  Hinges, so big they would dwarf a giant, almost
seem to creak and groan at the effort of holding the doors, nay, the dam in
place.  There seems to be no way of opening it to find out what is beyond...
Shame.
  }
  sector { cavern }
  flags { indoors }
  exits {
	to { n, 59 }
	  key { 60004 }
	  info { door, closed, locked, pickproof, autoclose, autolock }
	  keywords { gates }
	to { s, 57 }
  }
}

59
{
  name { The Imprisonment of Tiamat  }
  desc {
"   You are standing in a giant, egg-shaped prison hewn from the rock.  Drow
like runes and symbols burn, spit and blister upon every surface, even the
floor itself, singeing your feet and sending shocks up your legs.  Five mighty
chains have been anchored in to the walls at even intervals, each loop bigger
than you will ever be, and they connect together to form a bond powerful enough
to chain a Goddess.  This can only be the be place that Tiamat herself has been
imprisoned.  Two alcoves, too small for Tiamat to enter, have been dug in to
the northwest and northeast walls.  They may well offer sanctuary to any soul
unfortunate enough to find themselves in this place.
  }
  flags { no_sum, no_magic, private }
  sector { fire }
  exits {
	to { northwest, 50 }
	to { northeast, 55 }
  }
}

60
{
  name { Inside the Fire Caves  }
  desc {
"   You are standing at a turning inside the fire caves.  From here you can
feel the hot blast of heat emanating from the north, where something special
clearly happens.  The noise level is also rising, and you can hear the voice
of giants from all around you.  Perhaps there is a hub of some kind away to
the north?
  }
  flags { private }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
	to { n, 61 }
	to { e, 49 }
  }
}

61
{
  name { Rune Covered Chamber  }
  desc {
"   You stand within a large chamber lit by the glow of hundreds and thousands
of red hot blistering runes that have been carved in to the walls.  No matter
how hard you try you cannot decipher these runes.  One thing is for certain,
they are Drow in origin.  Why and what for, we may never know.
  }
  flags { no_mob, no_sum, dispel_magic }
  sector { cavern }
  exits {
	to { n, 62 }
	to { s, 60 }
  }
}

62
{
  name { The Throne of Fire  }
  desc {
This is the Throne of the Fire Giant King.  From here he (or sometimes a queen),
rules the caves with a iron (or fire) fist.  Many tables and benches have been
laid out, as if constant feasting and merry making takes place here.  And, as if
you didn't guess, there is a place laid for someone not of giant size.  Behind
the throne a series of the same blistering red hot runes forms another rune on
the wall.
  }
  sector { Fire }
  flags { no_magic, private }
  exits {
	to { s, 61 }
  }
}

63
{
  name { Ice Crown  }
  desc {
"   You are standing inside a vast icy cavern inside a glacier.  Known only
as 'Ice Crown', this giant hollow is the home of the Frost Giants and their
Jarl.  From here the giants roam out in to the Tundra in search of prey and
to guard their land from intruders.  A chair formed from jagged spears of
ice dominates the northern end of the cave, a possible throne for a powerful
Jarl?
  }
  sector { arctic }
  flags { private, indoors, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { s, 18 }
  }
  extra {
	keywords { throne ice chair spears }
	desc { 
"
This is a chair formed from hundreds, if not thousands, of jagged, sharp
shards of ice.  Anyone sitting on it is likely to get a sore bottom.

"	}  
  }
}

64
{
  name { The Eggy Chamber  }
  desc {
"   Eggs, eggs, eggs.  They are the size of your fist and they stretch
around the whole of this room.  Clearly this is where Gnatt lays her
eggs.  The air in here is fetid, foul, disgusting.  It's so full of
moisture and sulphur that you could choke on the fumes!
  }
  sector { gas }
  flags { private, indoors, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { 10, 34 }
	info { message }
	keywords { nest }
  }
  extra {
  	keywords { _ex10 }
  	desc {  "
	
#{yellow}You shimmy in to the crack and pop out who knows where!#{o}

"   }  
  }
}

65
{
  name { Upon the Cloud Tops  }
  desc {
"   You are standing on top of the clouds at the top of the valley.
They are firm yet spongey beneath your feet and range in colour
from dark grey to pale blue.  Soft wisps seem to break off and
reattach even as you watch.  The clouds swirl out south and east
of here, forming a vortex that curls back around to the north in
an anti-clockwise motion.  The rest of the cloud-scape, and the
valley floor, is obscured by the misty greyness.  You can also
skip back over to the valley top if you're scared.
  }
  sector { cloud }
  flags { private, no_sum, no_mob }
  exits {
	to { 10, 35 }
	  info { message }
	  keywords { valley }
	to { southeast, 66 }
  }
  extra {
  	keywords { _ex10 }
  	desc {  "
	
#{cyan}You skip lightly back on to the valley top!#{o}

"   }  
  }
}

66
{
  name { Upon a Cloud  }
  desc {
"   You are standing on a thin stream of cloudy mist and vapour that
somehow supports your enormous weight (har har).  The wisps of
cloudy mist feel spongey but safe.  You can exit east and head
further in to the swirling maelstrom that leads, eventually, to
the thick black clouds at the centre or head west and towards
the valley top.  But west is only for cowards - just so you
know.
  }
  sector { cloud }
  flags { private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { northwest, 65 }
	to { e, 67 }
  }  
}

67
{
  name { Upon a Cloud  }
  desc {
"   You float high in the sky like a bird on the wing.  And if it
wasn't for the almost insubstantial wisp of cloud beneath your
feet you'd surely be falling like a rock through the air.  At
this point you can see the valley below, spread it like some
sort of miniture model.  Ant-sized giants wander the paths and
go about their mundane existence.  So the south you can even
spy the distant fields of ice that mark the vast tundra of the
ice giants.  But to the north all you can see is the swirling
black maelstrom of the storm clouds.  You can exit east on to
darker grey clouds or head west towards the valley top.
  }
  sector { cloud }
  flags { private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { w, 66 }
	to { e, 68 }
  }  
}

68
{
  name { Upon a Dark Cloud  }
  desc {
"   You are standing on a dark grey cloud.  It feels spongey and
bouncy underfoot.  Thin tendrils and wisps break away and 
merge again, giving the feeling that this whole cloudscape
is somehow a living thing.  The mire beneath your feet is
too murky to see through and gaze at the valley below.  You
can exit here and head west, towards the valley top, but
you know in your heart that way is for losers.  Or you can
exit northeast and head in to the swirling chaos at the very
centre of the growing storm.

}
  sector { cloud }
  flags { private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { w, 67 }
	to { northeast, 69 }
  }  
}

69
{
  name { Edge of The Swirling Storm  }
  desc {
"   You are standing on the very edge of a swirling maelstrom
that flashes and growls angrily like a Goddess awoken from
her slumber ten minutes too early with no sign of a coffee
anywhere.  You can feel the rumble beneath you feet as it
sends shock waves through the storm.  To the northwest the
ground illuminates in bright strobes, each flash accompanied
by a sinister crack of thunder.  It might be better to head
back to the southwest and the safety of the valley top.  It's
okay to be a coward.
}
  sector { cloud }
  flags { private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { southwest, 68 }
	to { northwest, 75 }
	to { n, 70 }
  }  
}

70
{
  name { Edge of The Swirling Storm  }
  desc {

"   This is the edge of the swirling storm that seems to be
forever frozen above the valley.  Try as you might, you can't
seem to leap off to your death so I'd stop if I were you.  To
the west and northwest the clouds become more dense and dark,
angrier in a way.  Lightning flashes here and there and the
crash of thunder is loud in your ears.  You can exit to the
southwest and toward the valley top, leaving this cloud scape
like a running coward, or head west or northwest, further in
to the maelstrom. 
}
  sector { cloud }
  flags { private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { s, 69 }
	to { northwest, 71 }
	to { w, 75 }
  }  
}

71
{
  name { Edge of The Swirling Storm  }
  desc {

"   You are standing on the northern edge of a swirling mass
of storm clouds.  Lightning and thunder rage all around you,
filling the air with the taste of tin.  To the southwest the
eye of the storm is hidden by a shroud of mist that can only
be penetrated by walking through it.  You could do that, or
you could move along the edge of the storm as you see fit.  No
one would call you a coward for leaving this place... 
}
  sector { cloud }
  flags { private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { southwest, 76 }
	to { w, 72 }
	to { s, 75 }
	to { southeast, 70 }
  }  
}

72
{
  name { Edge of The Swirling Storm  }
  desc {

"   You are standing on the northwestern edge of a swirling
storm.  Insubstantial storm clouds, dark and heavy with rain
the promise of destruction, are all that hold you up in this
place.  The eye of the storm is directly south of you.  You
can also exit southwest, east or southeast as you see fit. 
}
  sector { cloud }
  flags { private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { southwest, 73 }
	to { e, 71 }
	to { s, 76 }
	to { southeast, 75 }
  }  
}

73
{
  name { Edge of The Swirling Storm  }
  desc {

"   You are perched on the very western edge of a swirling mass
of storm clouds that swirl anti-clockwise above the rocky valley
below.  The air is filled with the crash of thunder and the flashes
of lightning, leaving the air tasting metallic and tangy, as if you
have been licking tin and chewing on wool.  The eye of the storm
lies directly to the east of you, obscured by thick mists.  The
edges of the maelstrom spread out southwest and northwest. 
}
  sector { cloud }
  flags { private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { southeast, 74 }
	to { e, 76 }
	to { northeast, 72 }
  }  
}

74
{
  name { Edge of The Swirling Storm  }
  desc {
"   You are standing on the very edge of a swirling chaotic storm
that rages above the stony valley of giants below you.  The clouds
are spongey and springy under your feet yet the moisture they hold
still manages to soak your toes.  This is no place to be standing
around idly enjoying the views.  Away to the south, far out of range
for a leap, the tethering, fluffy trail of the storm seems hooked to
the valley tops somehow whilst to the north the eye of the storm is
obscured by thick mists. 
}
  sector { cloud }
  flags { private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { northwest, 73 }
	to { northeast, 75 }
	to { n, 76 }
  }  
}

75
{
  name { Edge of The Swirling Storm  }
  desc {
"   The clouds rush beneath your feet here, being sucked from the
southwest before being flung east towards the eye of the storm. 
You cannot penetrate the eye, but darker shadows seem to move within
it, as if it is alive in some way... 
}
  sector { cloud }
  flags { private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { n, 71 }
	to { northwest, 72 }
	to { w, 76 }
	to { southwest, 74 }
	to { southeast, 69 }
	to { e, 70 }
  }  
}

76
{
  name { In the Eye of the Storm  }
  desc {
"   You are standing in the eye of the storm.  Everything is calm in
here, the wind is silent, the thunder a long forgotten memory, the
lightning a mere atmospheric glow.  All around you can see the mists
that enclose this place, that protect it and keep it secret.  Below
your feet is nothing but air.  And yet you can walk on it just fine.
In the centre of the eye a dias of bright, glowing, fluffy cloud
rises in to a throne-like shape...
}
  sector { cloud }
  flags { private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { n, 72 }
	to { w, 73 }
	to { s, 74 }
	to { e, 75 }
	to { northeast, 71 }
  }  
}


77
{
  name { Inside a Roundhouse  }
  desc {
"   You are standing inside a roundhouse on the valley road in the mountain
stronghold known as Pyragard.  Whomever, or whatever, lives here is a slob.
The dishes are unwashed and discarded over the floor.  Dirty, used clothing
is spread about and acts like a treacherous (and possibly sticky) carpet.
Yuck.  Why would you want to live in a place like this?  There isn't even
a window to let that awful smell out.  Gah!  You can exit back through the
opening to the valley road.
  }
  sector { ship_deck }
  flags { indoors }
  exits {
	to { 10, 28 }
	  keywords { opening }
  }
}